      "id": "1773160995594-9tjmhstpc",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I found the problems. Here's what's going wrong with auto play and keys/locked doors:\n\n1. **Auto play doesn't pick up keys** - The `PICKUP_TYPES` list on line 179 of autoplay.ts doesn't include `'key'`, so the auto player walks right past keys on the ground.\n\n2. **Auto play can't pathfind through locked doors** - The `pathTo` function uses `isWalkableTile`, and `LockedDoor` is NOT considered walkable (see dungeon.ts line 193-196). So even when the player has the right key, auto play can't find a path to anything behind a locked door.\n\n3. **Auto play doesn't specifically seek out locked doors to open them** - There's no step to go unlock vault doors when the player is holding the matching key.\n\nLet me fix all three issues.",
