    {
      "id": "1773161111580-zaylep5yh",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "All fixed! Here's what was causing auto play to freak out with keys and locked doors:\n\n1. **Auto play wasn't picking up keys** - It would walk right past keys on the ground because keys weren't in its list of items worth grabbing. Fixed that so it now picks them up.\n\n2. **Auto play couldn't find a path through locked doors** - Even when holding the right key, the pathfinding treated locked doors as impassable walls, so the player would get stuck or wander aimlessly. Now it recognizes locked doors as passable when the player has the matching key.\n\n3. **Auto play didn't actively go to locked doors** - Added a new step where auto play will head to a locked door and open it when it has the right key, instead of ignoring it completely.\n\nEverything builds cleanly. Give it a try and let me know if it's working better now!",
